MIT License

This project, "nanogpt-1gpu", is a single-GPU adaptation of the modded-nanogpt
speedrun, built for local experimentation, screening, and learning. It descends from:

  - Andrej Karpathy's nanoGPT and llm.c — the original lineage and the
    124M-parameter / FineWeb / 3.28-validation-loss target.
  - Keller Jordan and the modded-nanogpt contributors — the speedrun architecture
    (RoPE/YaRN, value/bigram embeddings, paired-head attention, skip/backout) and the
    Muon / NorMuon optimizer. https://github.com/KellerJordan/modded-nanogpt

The single-GPU harness, the experimental methodology, the results, and the bug log are
original to this repository. Portions of the model and optimizer are adapted from
modded-nanogpt and remain under its MIT license, reproduced below.

